ers rearranging themselves to pay you back in some future coin you will not like. The Conclave opens a quiet inquiry that will take too long but not forever, and in the meantime a whisper spreads that Aren Siltwarden reads contracts as well as currents. You leave the ledge with more allies than you climbed with, and also with the sense that some door elsewhere has closed without a sound.\"\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M5\"], \"next\": [\"M7\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"currency\", \"description\": \"25 coin stipend for escort and negotiation at the Fault.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"item\", \"description\": \"Obsidian Bearing Kit (improves mobility on slick stone).\"},\n        {\"type\": \"item\", \"description\": \"Syndic’s Iron Chit (trade goodwill at Seven-Kettle stalls).\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"description\": \"Emberlight Artificers +3.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"description\": \"Seven-Kettle Syndic +2.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"description\": \"Temple of the Nine Tides +1.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"access\", \"description\": \"Supervised access to the Obsidian Fault observation ledges.\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"